For Teacher Appreciation Week, TODAY, (Thursday), we celebrate the imagination that your Teachers encourage in you everyday. "Oh the Places You'll Go".....

If you could go anywhere in the world, where would you go? What would you wear? What would you take with you? Who would you go with? What would you eat? Take an "Imagination Vacation" and tell us about it, share your adventure with your family, or send a pic showcasing your creativity.

Have fun taking a quiet moment, closing your eyes and using your wildest IMAGINATION!

post_text:
Meet the principal!

Miss Alison Roberts has been part of the Newfound family since the 2017-2018 school year. She earned her undergraduate degree from Houghton College in Houghton, NY and taught middle school and high school physical education and health for nine years in NH before working as a K-8 assistant principal. She served as an assistant principal for seven years before joining the Newfound Area School District as the principal of Danbury Elementary School. Miss Roberts also attended Plymouth State University where she earned her M.Ed, CAGS, and her Ed.D in Educational Leadership.

When not collaborating with teachers and talking with parents and students, Miss Roberts enjoys spending time outside with her family, friends, and her dogs. During the summer months, you may find her fishing on the riverbanks or riding the dirt bike trails. During the winter she enjoys snowboarding and snowshoeing.
